<meta charset="utf-8" />
<title>Experiment Report — {{ result.name }}</title>
<style>
  :root { --accent: #2563eb; --flat: #dc2626; --ink: #1e293b; --muted: #64748b; --line: #e2e8f0; --bg: #ffffff; --panel: #f8fafc; }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
         color: var(--ink); background: var(--bg); margin: 0; line-height: 1.5; }
  .wrap { max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 24px 64px; }
  h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; margin: 0 0 4px; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 32px 0 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); padding-bottom: 6px; }
  .type-chip { display: inline-block; background: var(--accent); color: #fff; font-size: 0.72rem;
               font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.03em; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 999px;
               vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 8px; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .meta { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.85rem; margin: 4px 0 0; }
  .callout { background: var(--panel); border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); padding: 12px 16px;
             border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 12px 0; }
  .callout.warn { border-left-color: var(--flat); }
  pre { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 6px; padding: 14px;
        overflow-x: auto; font-size: 0.82rem; }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: 0.86rem; }
  th, td { text-align: right; padding: 8px 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  th:first-child, td:first-child { text-align: left; }
  thead th { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--line); }
  tr.flat td { background: #fef2f2; font-weight: 600; }
  .chart { margin: 8px 0; }
  footer { margin-top: 40px; padding-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
           color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.8rem; }
  code { background: var(--panel); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .machine { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--muted); }
  .machine dt { font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); display: inline; }
  .machine dd { display: inline; margin: 0 16px 0 4px; }
</style>

<div class="wrap">
  <h1>{{ result.name }}<span class="type-chip">{{ result.experiment_type }}</span></h1>
  <p class="meta">
    {{ result.timestamp }} &middot; config <code>{{ result.short_hash }}</code>
    &middot; {{ result.dataset_summary.n_docs }} docs / {{ result.dataset_summary.n_queries }} queries
    &middot; {{ result.repetitions }} repetitions
  </p>
  <p class="meta">
    {{ result.machine_info.cpu }} &middot; {{ result.machine_info.ram_gb }} GB RAM
    &middot; Python {{ result.machine_info.python }} &middot; FAISS {{ result.machine_info.faiss }}
  </p>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <pre>{{ config_yaml }}</pre>

  <h2>What is measured</h2>
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Recall@{{ k }} (vs exact search).</strong> Measures how faithfully HNSW approximates
    exact search on the same embeddings; it does <em>not</em> measure retrieval quality against
    human relevance judgments. Flat (exact) search is the ground truth, so its recall is 1.0 by
    definition.
  </div>
  {% if result.synthetic %}
  <div class="callout warn">
    <strong>Synthetic random vectors</strong> — for smoke-testing the pipeline, not for drawing
    conclusions. Normalized random high-dimensional vectors are near-equidistant, so nearest
    neighbors are essentially arbitrary and HNSW recall may look anomalous.
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Config</th>
        <th>Recall@{{ k }}</th>
        <th>p50 (ms)</th>
        <th>p95 (ms)</th>
        <th>IQR (ms)</th>
        <th>Build (s)</th>
        <th>Size (MB)</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in rows %}
      <tr class="{{ 'flat' if row.is_flat else '' }}">
        <td>{{ row.label }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.recall }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.p50 }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.p95 }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.iqr }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.build }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.size }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Recall vs Latency (Pareto)</h2>
  <div class="chart">{{ chart_html | safe }}</div>
  <p class="meta">
    Variance across repetitions reflects HNSW's sensitivity to vector insertion order; builds are
    single-threaded for reproducibility. Recall error bars = across-repetition std; latency error
    bars = within-run per-query IQR.
  </p>

  <h2>Machine</h2>
  <dl class="machine">
    <dt>CPU</dt><dd>{{ result.machine_info.cpu }}</dd>
    <dt>RAM</dt><dd>{{ result.machine_info.ram_gb }} GB</dd>
    <dt>Platform</dt><dd>{{ result.machine_info.platform }}</dd>
    <dt>Python</dt><dd>{{ result.machine_info.python }}</dd>
    <dt>FAISS</dt><dd>{{ result.machine_info.faiss }}</dd>
    <dt>numpy</dt><dd>{{ result.machine_info.numpy }}</dd>
    <dt>torch</dt><dd>{{ result.machine_info.torch }}</dd>
  </dl>
  <p class="meta">Laptop-grade measurements; background load is not controlled.</p>

  <footer>
    VectorBench v{{ version }} &middot; experiment type <code>{{ result.experiment_type }}</code>
    &middot; full config hash <code>{{ result.full_hash }}</code><br />
    Reproduce: <code>{{ reproduce_cmd }}</code>
  </footer>
</div>
